.TH "dpni_get_port_mac_addr" 9 "dpni_get_port_mac_addr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dpni_get_port_mac_addr \- Retrieve MAC address associated to the physical port the DPNI is attached to
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dpni_get_port_mac_addr
.BI "(struct fsl_mc_io *mc_io "  ","
.BI "u32 cmd_flags "  ","
.BI "u16 token "  ","
.BI "u8 mac_addr[6] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mc_io" 12
Pointer to MC portal's I/O object
.IP "cmd_flags" 12
Command flags; one or more of 'MC_CMD_FLAG_'
.IP "token" 12
Token of DPNI object
.IP "mac_addr" 12
MAC address of the physical port, if any, otherwise 0
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The primary MAC address is not cleared by this operation.
.SH "RETURN"
'0' on Success; Error code otherwise.
